<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-15051] Camel GIT component does not check out the branch specified in branchName when cloning</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-15051</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When cloning a repository from a server (tested with GitHub) with the following Camel endpoint/options:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;git:///F:\localpath?operation=clone&amp;amp;remotePath=&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/xxxxxxxx/cust-ir.git&amp;amp;username=xxxxxxxx&amp;amp;password=yyyyyyyy&amp;amp;remoteName=origin&amp;amp;branchName=branch_uat&amp;amp;synchronous=true&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/xxxxxxxx/cust-ir.git&amp;amp;username=xxxxxxxx&amp;amp;password=yyyyyyyy&amp;amp;remoteName=origin&amp;amp;branchName=branch_uat&amp;amp;synchronous=true&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The remote repository was correctly cloned to the localpath, but the branch specified is not created locally and not checked out.&#160; The localpath working copy is the master branch.&#160; Since Camel GIT does not have a checkout command, one would have to manually checkout the branch thus defeat the purpose of using the component.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;This was tested on Windows 10 Pro with Camel 3.2.0 (Spring Boot 2.2.6) against GitHub.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="13304190">CAMEL-15051</key>
